# Hybrid Marketplace Mobile Application
## System Blueprint

---

# 1. Project Overview

The Hybrid Marketplace Mobile Application is a peer-to-peer mobile platform that enables users to either sell second-hand items or exchange them with other users. The application aims to provide a flexible marketplace where users can choose between selling items for money or trading them with other items.

The platform addresses the issue of unused household items by allowing users to easily redistribute them within the community. By supporting both selling and item exchange, the system improves transaction flexibility and encourages product reuse.

The mobile application is developed using **Flutter**, while the backend server manages business logic and communicates with a **MySQL database**.

---

# 2. System Objectives

- Provide a platform for users to sell or exchange second-hand items
- Increase transaction flexibility through hybrid selling and trading
- Encourage reuse of items and reduce waste
- Provide structured transaction management between users
- Enable communication between users through messaging and support services

---

# 3. Core System Modules

## 3.1 User Profile Module

The User Profile Module manages user accounts and personal information while also providing features that improve item discovery.

### Features

- User registration and login
- Profile information management
- View user posted items
- View user transaction history
- Item discovery through swipe-based browsing

### Swiping Item Feature

To improve item discovery, the system provides a swipe-based browsing interface where users can quickly explore items.

Users can:
- Swipe right to show interest in an item
- Swipe left to skip the item
- View the next item card instantly

This interaction allows users to browse many items efficiently and provides a more engaging experience compared to traditional scrolling.

### Main Functions

- Create user account
- Retrieve user profile data
- Update profile information
- Delete account
- Record user item interactions

---

## 3.2 Item Listing Module

The Item Listing Module allows users to create and manage item listings in the marketplace.

### Features

- Create new item listing
- Upload item images
- Add item description and category
- Select listing type (Sell / Trade / Both)
- Edit or delete listings
- Browse and view item details

### Main Functions

- Create item listing
- Retrieve item listings
- Update listing details
- Delete listing

---

## 3.3 Transaction Request Module

The Transaction Request Module manages the process of sending and managing purchase or trade requests between users.

Instead of separating purchase and trade systems, the application uses a unified transaction request model.

### Features

- Send purchase request
- Send trade request
- Accept or reject requests
- View incoming transaction requests
- View outgoing transaction requests
- Track request status (Pending, Accepted, Rejected)

### Main Functions

- Create transaction request
- Retrieve transaction requests
- Update transaction request status
- Cancel transaction request

---

## 3.4 Messaging Module

The Messaging Module allows users to communicate directly with each other and also provides automated assistance through an AI chatbot.

### Features

- Private messaging between users
- Chat history storage
- Conversation list
- Item-related discussions
- AI-powered customer service chatbot

### AI Chatbox Customer Service

The system integrates an AI chatbot within the messaging module to assist users with common questions and provide platform guidance.

The AI chatbot can help users with:

- Posting items
- Sending transaction requests
- Understanding trading procedures
- Navigating application features

This provides immediate support to users without requiring manual customer service assistance.

### Main Functions

- Create chat session
- Send and receive messages
- Retrieve message history
- Provide automated AI assistance

