# 8. Project Folder Structure (MVVM)

The Flutter mobile application follows the MVVM pattern with Provider for state management.

```
lib/
├── main.dart                          # App entry point
│
├── core/                              # Shared app-wide resources
│   ├── constants/                     # Colors, strings, route names, etc.
│   ├── theme/                         # App theme (light/dark)
│   └── utils/                         # Helper functions / extensions
│
├── models/                            # Data models (pure Dart classes)
│   │   User, Item, TransactionRequest, Chat, Message
│
├── views/                             # UI layer
│   ├── screens/                       # Full-page screens grouped by module
│   │   ├── auth/                      # Login, Register screens
│   │   ├── home/                      # Home / feed screen
│   │   ├── explore/                   # Swipe-based item browsing
│   │   ├── item/                      # Item detail, create & edit listing
│   │   ├── profile/                   # User profile & history
│   │   ├── transaction/               # Transaction requests (in/out)
│   │   └── chat/                      # Messaging & AI chatbot
│   └── widgets/
│       └── common/                    # Reusable shared widgets
│
├── viewmodels/                        # Business logic & state (Provider)
│   │   AuthViewModel, ItemViewModel,
│   │   TransactionViewModel, ChatViewModel
│
├── repositories/                      # Data access layer
│   │   Bridges ViewModels ↔ Services
│   │   UserRepository, ItemRepository,
│   │   TransactionRepository, ChatRepository
│
├── services/                          # External communication
│   │   REST API calls, WebSocket/Socket.IO,
│   │   ApiService, AuthService, SocketService
│
└── routes/                            # Named route definitions / app router
```

## Layer Responsibilities

| Layer | Folder | Responsibility |
|---|---|---|
| Model | `models/` | Data structures only, no logic |
| View | `views/` | Flutter widgets, UI rendering |
| ViewModel | `viewmodels/` | State management via Provider |
| Repository | `repositories/` | Fetches/caches data from services |
| Service | `services/` | HTTP / WebSocket calls to backend |
| Core | `core/` | Shared constants, theme, utilities |